:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>S7.1bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde92c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f375b208-e298-4f39-9775-73bec2dbb277</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>160</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9:2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf:0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing of Destination Data Store Backup Storage</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Backup Storage may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to data being written to the attacker's target instead of Backup Storage. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the destination data store.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>S7.1</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>T18bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde92c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f375b208-e298-4f39-9775-73bec2dbb277</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>161</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9:2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf:0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>The Backup Storage Data Store Could Be Corrupted</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering is the act of altering the bits. Tampering with a process involves changing bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Data flowing across Binary may be tampered with by an attacker. This may lead to corruption of Backup Storage. Ensure the integrity of the data flow to the data store.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>T18</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>R8bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde92c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f375b208-e298-4f39-9775-73bec2dbb277</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>162</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9:2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf:0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Store Denies Backup Storage Potentially Writing Data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Repudiation</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Repudiation threats involve an adversary denying that something happened.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Backup Storage claims that it did not write data received from an entity on the other side of the trust boundary. Consider using logging or auditing to record the source, time, and summary of the received data.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>R8</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>I6bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde92c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f375b208-e298-4f39-9775-73bec2dbb277</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>163</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9:2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf:0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Flow Sniffing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Information Disclosure</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Information disclosure happens when the information can be read by an unauthorized party.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Data flowing across Binary may be sniffed by an attacker. Depending on what type of data an attacker can read, it may be used to attack other parts of the system or simply be a disclosure of information leading to compliance violations. Consider encrypting the data flow.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>I6</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>D2bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde92c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f375b208-e298-4f39-9775-73bec2dbb277</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>164</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9:2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf:0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Potential Excessive Resource Consumption for Cloud Infrastructure or Backup Storage</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Denial Of Service</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Denial of Service happens when the process or a datastore is not able to service incoming requests or perform up to spec.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Does Cloud Infrastructure or Backup Storage take explicit steps to control resource consumption? Resource consumption attacks can be hard to deal with, and there are times that it makes sense to let the OS do the job. Be careful that your resource requests don't deadlock, and that they do timeout.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>D2</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>D4bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde92c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f375b208-e298-4f39-9775-73bec2dbb277</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>165</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9:2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf:0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Flow Binary Is Potentially Interrupted</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Denial Of Service</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Denial of Service happens when the process or a datastore is not able to service incoming requests or perform up to spec.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>An external agent interrupts data flowing across a trust boundary in either direction.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>D4</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>D5bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde92c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f375b208-e298-4f39-9775-73bec2dbb277</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>166</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9:2c86c34e-f551-4662-99d4-db566077bebf:0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Store Inaccessible</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Denial Of Service</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Denial of Service happens when the process or a datastore is not able to service incoming requests or perform up to spec.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>An external agent prevents access to a data store on the other side of the trust boundary.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>bc26da4f-c081-4b60-bf0b-1f4d5be7fde9</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>0211c5cd-ecfa-4dc6-b8d6-fb8784beb2a1</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>D5</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>T221100a18-2c24-4552-84fa-11e21abb76af8b988510-8da5-411f-a582-4a1e9af8c28482ceafe9-ea4b-41f9-9200-86b17b49ffd8</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f375b208-e298-4f39-9775-73bec2dbb277</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>8b988510-8da5-411f-a582-4a1e9af8c284</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>189</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>21100a18-2c24-4552-84fa-11e21abb76af:8b988510-8da5-411f-a582-4a1e9af8c284:82ceafe9-ea4b-41f9-9200-86b17b49ffd8</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Medical Device Gateway Process Memory Tampered</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering is the act of altering the bits. Tampering with a process involves changing bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>If Medical Device Gateway is given access to memory, such as shared memory or pointers, or is given the ability to control what EHR Management System executes (for example, passing back a function pointer.), then Medical Device Gateway can tamper with EHR Management System. Consider if the function could work with less access to memory, such as passing data rather than pointers. Copy in data provided, and then validate it.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>HTTPS</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>21100a18-2c24-4552-84fa-11e21abb76af</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>82ceafe9-ea4b-41f9-9200-86b17b49ffd8</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>T2</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>T13.121100a18-2c24-4552-84fa-11e21abb76af8b988510-8da5-411f-a582-4a1e9af8c28482ceafe9-ea4b-41f9-9200-86b17b49ffd8</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f375b208-e298-4f39-9775-73bec2dbb277</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>8b988510-8da5-411f-a582-4a1e9af8c284</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>190</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>21100a18-2c24-4552-84fa-11e21abb76af:8b988510-8da5-411f-a582-4a1e9af8c284:82ceafe9-ea4b-41f9-9200-86b17b49ffd8</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Cross Site Scripting</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering is the act of altering the bits. Tampering with a process involves changing bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>The web server 'EHR Management System' could be a subject to a cross-site scripting attack because it does not sanitize untrusted input.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>HTTPS</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>21100a18-2c24-4552-84fa-11e21abb76af</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>82ceafe9-ea4b-41f9-9200-86b17b49ffd8</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>T13.1</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>E521100a18-2c24-4552-84fa-11e21abb76af8b988510-8da5-411f-a582-4a1e9af8c28482ceafe9-ea4b-41f9-9200-86b17b49ffd8</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>f375b208-e298-4f39-9775-73bec2dbb277</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>8b988510-8da5-411f-a582-4a1e9af8c284</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>191</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>21100a18-2c24-4552-84fa-11e21abb76af:8b988510-8da5-411f-a582-4a1e9af8c284:82ceafe9-ea4b-41f9-9200-86b17b49ffd8</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Using Impersonation</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Of Privilege</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>A user subject gains increased capability or privilege by taking advantage of an implementation bug.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>EHR Management System may be able to impersonate the context of Medical Device Gateway in order to gain additional privilege.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>HTTPS</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>21100a18-2c24-4552-84fa-11e21abb76af</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>82ceafe9-ea4b-41f9-9200-86b17b49ffd8</b:TargetGu